author: National Geographic
description:
Bertie heads to South Africa for his most audacious mission yet. The wild waters here are a hotspot for one of the ocean’s most famous and feared predators, the Great White Shark. Diving in the shallows without a cage, Bertie will attempt to film these huge sharks hunting seals. By entering their domain, he discovers the challenges they face on our rapidly changing planet.

author: National Geographic
description:
This summer, SHARKFEST returns with over 25 hours of hair-raising, shark-infested programming that brings viewers closer than ever to the ocean’s fiercest fish. The fin-credible lineup includes “Sharks Up Close,” where wildlife filmmaker Bertie Gregory embarks on a daring cage-free dive to capture the raw power and beauty of great whites on film, and “JAWS @ 50: The Definitive Inside Story,” the authorized documentary marking the 50th anniversary of the film that redefined Hollywood, launched the summer blockbuster, and helped spark a global movement in shark conservation. Other series include “Investigation Shark Attack,” “Super Shark Highway,” “Shark Quest: Hunt for the Apex Predator” and “Sharks of the North,” with each offering thrilling encounters and cutting-edge science. From awe-inspiring adventures to myth-busting insights, SHARKFEST 2025 is the ultimate deep dive into the science, power and magnificence of these misunderstood predators.
